#Text=Claire Holley
#Text=Claire Chamblin Holley is an American folk singer-songwriter from Mississippi .
#Text=She has released eight albums and written for TV , Hollywood musicals and museums .
#Text=She tours nationwide , is a wife and mom , and makes her home in Los Angeles , California .
#Text=Life and career
#Text=Holley grew up in Jackson , Mississippi where at an early age she learned to play the auto-harp , ukulele , piano , and guitar ; though it was playing guitar that really piqued her interest .
#Text=She has said , " I was never that good at playing piano , and maybe that 's because I did n't practice enough , but I found the guitar fun to play .

#Text=She was commissioned to write original music for Arlene Hutton ’ s play  See Rock City " which premiered at the Crossley Theatre in Hollywood September 2006 and LA Weekly magazine nominated her for " Best Original Music " for the LA Weekly theatre awards for the " See Rock City " songs . [ 2 ] [ 3 ]

column1: #Text=Acoustic Guitar Magazine wrote , " Claire Holley is an observer , a romantic reporter from the backyards and front porches of the heartland . " [ 4 ]

#Text=Claire Holley has performed with Mary Chapin Carpenter , Kate Campbell , and Caroline Herring , and has composed music for The Fence , an independent film which received the 2008 UCLA Directors Spotlight Award . [ 5 ]
#Text=Mary Chapin Carpenter has said that Holley has an angelic style of writing . [ 6 ]
#Text=Two of her songs have appeared in the ABC TV show Men In Trees [ 7 ] [ 8 ] and she wrote the original music for the documentary Looking For Lurch in 2008 . [ 9 ]

#Text=Holley was also a member of Musette ( formerly Song Sirens ) , a group of female singer-songwriters that performed every so often in Sierra Madre , a little town in the mountains just north of Los Angeles . [ 5 ]
#Text=In 2013 she formed the group Powdercoat and released a duet EP with fellow songwriter Kristin Mooney .
#Text=The Huffington Post called it " one of the year 's loveliest recordings . " [ 10 ]
#Text=Holley announced that her eighth studio album , " Time in the Middle , " will be released in June 2015 .
#Text=It was recorded at Sonic Temple studio in Ferndale , CA . [ 11 ]
#Text=Ms. Holley now lives in the Los Angeles area with her husband , Chad . [ 1 ]
